The total number of confirmed cases of coronavirus in South Africa is now standing at 402 people. This means there has been an increase of 128 from Sunday’s announcement. The minister of health Dr Zweli Mkhize said it is notable that Northern Cape has its first corona case. Ramaphosa to address the nation tonight! “As has been announced that president Ramaphosa will address the nation on measures to be undertaken to mitigate the impact of corona, we will there after engage the public to give further details and explanations on the results including the significant rise, the ongoing processes and each province’s progress on contact tracing efforts,” said Mkhize. 